    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_b0eaa65c-4018-4e09-9edd-8546794c418c" class="text-block-content">
    <p>As an instructor, you may be able to display a theme designed for elementary-level users in your course. When enabled, this theme displays a font conducive to younger students and simplifies Course Navigation links. This theme is applied independently of any themes applied at the account level.</p>
<p><strong>Notes</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Canvas Elementary Theming is a feature option. Learn how to manage feature options in the <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-manage-feature-options-for-a-course/ta-p/710" target="_blank">course features</a> lesson. If the Canvas Elementary Theming option is not available in your course, your institution admin has disabled and locked it in the account.</li>
<li>Your institution may also enable an elementary setting for all of Canvas. If your course dashboard does not appear as displayed in these images, learn about the <a href="/t5/Canvas-for-Elementary-Basics/What-is-Canvas-for-Elementary/ta-p/496844" target="_blank">Canvas for Elementary</a> feature.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="view-course-font" data-step-uuid="91210480-da04-436a-a99d-7247cef618f1">
